cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with learning a generative model of 3D shapes from natural images using unsupervised learning. This involves using a generator network to create 3D objects and a differentiable renderer to produce images of these objects from random viewpoints. The paper is likely to be categorized under computer vision (cs.CV) as it deals with learning from images, and machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves the use of generative adversarial networks. It may also be categorized under graphics (cs.GR) as it involves the use of a renderer, artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves learning a generative model, and neural networks (cs.NE) as it involves the use of a generator network.
